---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import USBadge from '../components/USBadge.astro';
import TipChart from '../components/TipChart.astro';
import { tipping, usBaseline, tippingChecked } from '../data/tipping.js';

// Everything reads from tipping.js live. Nothing is re-typed here.
const rows = tipping;
const noTip = rows.filter(r => r.tierRank === 0);
const cashEssential = rows.filter(r => /essential/i.test(r.cashOrCard));
const chargeOnBill = rows.filter(r => r.serviceCharge !== 'rarely');
const canOffend = rows.filter(r => /^yes/i.test(r.canOffend));

function niceDate(iso) {
  if (!iso) return '';
  const d = new Date(iso + 'T00:00:00');
  if (isNaN(d.getTime())) return iso;
  return d.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long' });
}
const checkedLabel = niceDate(tippingChecked);

const title = 'Tipping by country: what to leave, compared to the US | True Trip Costs';
const description = 'What to tip in ' + rows.length + ' countries, measured against the US habit of ' + usBaseline.addsPercent + ' percent. Where a tip is unwelcome, where a service charge is already on the bill, and where you need cash. Checked ' + checkedLabel + '.';
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <Nav />
  <main class="wrap tip">
    <p class="ctx"><USBadge /> <span class="stamp">Checked {checkedLabel}</span></p>
    <h1>What do I tip here?</h1>
    <p class="tip-lede">
      Every country below, measured against what you already leave at home. Almost everywhere expects
      less, and in {noTip.length} places the answer is nothing at all.
    </p>

    <div class="tip-find">
      <label class="tip-find-lab" for="tip-filter">Going somewhere specific?</label>
      <input
        type="text"
        id="tip-filter"
        class="tip-find-in"
        placeholder="Type a country, like Japan"
        aria-label="Find a country in the tipping chart"
        autocomplete="off"
      />
    </div>

    <section class="tip-chart" aria-label="Usual tip by country">
      <TipChart rows={rows} baseline={usBaseline} id="tipchart" />
    </section>

    <p class="tip-trap">
      One thing that costs Americans money: in {chargeOnBill.length} of these countries a service charge is
      usually already printed on the bill, and tipping again on top is the most common expensive mistake.
      Check the bill before you add anything.
    </p>

    <div class="tip-honest">
      <p class="tip-honest-h">This is custom, not law</p>
      <p>
        Tipping norms are social habits, not published rules. They vary by region, venue and season, and a
        busy tourist strip behaves differently from a neighborhood place an hour away. That makes this a
        different kind of claim from our visa-fee and tourist-tax pages, where the figures come from
        government sources. Treat these as well-researched guidance to travel with, not as rules.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="tip-more" aria-labelledby="knowmore">
      <h2 id="knowmore">What the chart cannot show you</h2>

      <div class="tm">
        <h3>Where a tip is genuinely unwelcome</h3>
        <p>
          In {noTip.map(r => r.country).join(', ')}, leaving money is not the norm. That is not stinginess on
          your part, it is the local standard, and paying the exact amount is the correct thing to do.
          {canOffend.length > 0 && (
            <> In {canOffend.map(r => r.country).join(' and ')} a tip can actively land wrong: cash may be
            politely refused, and a sincere thank-you is the gesture that carries weight instead.</>
          )}
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tm">
        <h3>A service charge is not always a tip</h3>
        <p>
          This one inverts the American assumption. Taiwan treats the printed service charge as general
          restaurant revenue by law rather than a gratuity. In Egypt, Argentina, Georgia and Vietnam it
          commonly does not reach the worker either. So a charge on the bill does not reliably mean staff
          have been taken care of, and in those places a small amount handed directly to the server lands
          where the printed charge does not.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tm">
        <h3>Where you need actual cash</h3>
        <p>
          In {cashEssential.map(r => r.country).join(', ')} a tip realistically has to be cash. Argentina is
          the sharpest case: card terminals there have no tip line at all, so anything you mean for the
          server has to come out of your pocket. Carry small notes in these countries or you will end up
          leaving nothing by default.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tm">
        <h3>What this does to your budget</h3>
        <p>
          The practical version, which is what we actually care about here. Across Europe and Japan, budget
          almost nothing extra for tips: the price you see is close to the price you pay. Across North
          America and the Caribbean, add a real line item to every meal, because that is where tipping
          genuinely moves your daily spend. Everywhere else sits between the two, closer to nothing than to
          home.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="tm">
        <h3>Norms are moving, and mostly upward</h3>
        <p>
          Tipping shifts faster than most travel facts. Card terminals keep nudging suggested percentages up,
          which is quietly raising expectations in places that had none a decade ago. Turkey banned mandatory
          service charges in 2026. A 2025 Indian court ruling confirmed that service charges there are
          voluntary, not obligatory. We re-check this page as those norms move, and where sources disagreed
          we lowered our confidence rather than picking a number that looked tidy.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <p class="tip-foot">
      Compiled by the True Trip Costs desk and checked {checkedLabel}. Percentages are the usual restaurant
      tip for a US traveler, drawn from local guidance and industry sources rather than a single official
      register. Sourcing is not equally firm everywhere: most rows are well supported and carry no mark, a
      faint dot flags a figure we are less certain of, and a dashed bar flags the one country where sources
      genuinely conflicted. Country names link to our full money guide for that country.
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />

  <style>
    .tip{max-width:820px}
    .tip h1{margin-bottom:10px}
    .tip-lede{font-size:17.5px;color:#3B4A46;line-height:1.55;max-width:620px;margin:0 0 20px}

    .tip-find{margin:0 0 20px;max-width:420px}
    .tip-find-lab{display:block;font-size:12.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin:0 0 6px}
    .tip-find-in{width:100%;box-sizing:border-box;font:inherit;font-size:15px;color:var(--ink);background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:11px 14px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)}
    .tip-find-in:focus{outline:2px solid var(--amber);outline-offset:1px;border-color:var(--amber)}

    .tip-chart{margin:0 0 20px}

    .tip-trap{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.55;background:var(--amber-bg);border:1px solid var(--amber);border-radius:12px;padding:13px 16px;margin:0 0 24px;max-width:720px}

    .tip-honest{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-left:3px solid var(--teal);border-radius:12px;padding:14px 18px;margin:0 0 34px;max-width:720px;box-shadow:var(--shadow)}
    .tip-honest-h{font-size:12px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--teal-deep);margin:0 0 6px}
    .tip-honest p{font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.55;margin:0}

    .tip-more h2{font-family:var(--serif);font-weight:500;font-size:clamp(21px,3.2vw,28px);letter-spacing:-.01em;margin:0 0 16px}
    .tm{margin:0 0 22px;max-width:700px}
    .tm h3{font-size:15.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink);margin:0 0 6px}
    .tm p{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.6;margin:0}

    .tip-foot{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.55;margin:30px 0 8px;max-width:700px}

    @media (max-width:560px){
      .tip-lede{font-size:16.5px}
      .tm p{font-size:14px}
    }
  </style>

  <script is:inline>
    (function () {
      var input = document.getElementById('tip-filter');
      var list = document.getElementById('tipchart-rows');
      if (!input || !list) return;
      var rows = Array.prototype.slice.call(list.querySelectorAll('.tc-row'));
      var empty = document.getElementById('tipchart-empty');

      function norm(s) {
        return (s || '').toLowerCase().normalize('NFD').replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, '');
      }

      input.addEventListener('input', function () {
        var q = norm(input.value.trim());
        var shown = 0;
        rows.forEach(function (row) {
          var hit = q === '' || norm(row.getAttribute('data-name')).indexOf(q) !== -1;
          row.classList.toggle('is-hidden', !hit);
          if (hit) shown++;
        });
        if (empty) empty.hidden = shown !== 0;
      });
    })();
  </script>
</Base>
